Package Microssa

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Configuration
    This class reads in the configuration file, defaults values, and returns settings on request.
    Database
    This class is responsible for writing MatchingEngine events to a database.
    DepthBook
    This class implements a modified SkipList to keep track of a single side (Bid or Offer) of OrderIDs for a Symbol, and their relative order to each other based on Price and arrival order: first in, first out.
    FIXInterface
    This class is responsible for reading orders and writing matches and order events using the FIX protocol via the FIXApp class.
    Hooks
    These are customizable hooks to notify another system of the activities of the MatchingEngine.
    Logger
    This class is responsible for writing MatchingEngine events to a flatfile.
    Main
    Static class that initializes the MatchingEngine, Logger, OrderSocket and PriceSocket objects.
    MatchingEngine
    This class handles order input, matching, reporting, and market data.
    Order
    Object used to store order details.
    OrderSocket
    This class creates a TCP socket interface to allow new orders, amends, and cancel requests to be sent to the MatchingEngine.
    PriceSocket
    This class creates a TCP socket interface to allow market data subscribe/unsubscribe requests to be sent to the MatchingEngine.
